column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/p4525_d512534cd71ebdb67bf0cb2a377dc7c2b06ba438/ for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-te

Do we need this extra warning in addition to the **This is a pre-release test build - use at your own risk - do not use for mining or merchant applications** that already comes in pre-release builds by default?\n
Depends on how much this feature is going to be tested before 0.10.0 I suppose.\nShall I remove it?\n
Yeah, I think it's unnecessary. There are many things in ~~0.10~~ master that would require warnings otherwise :)\n
